The Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, has given the go ahead for worship places to reopen from August 7. The Governor said this on Saturday during his update on the Coronavirus Disease on the state. So also did Sanwo-Olu announce an increase in the number of public gatherings capacity from 20 people to 50. There had been agitations for the reopening of churches in Lagos State since the easing of the lockdown on the COVID-19 began. Theeagleonline The governor of Lagos state, Babajide Sanwo-Olu says worship centres in the state will be allowed to reopen from June 19. He said mosques are to reopen from June 19 while churches are to begin services from June 21. The governor gave this announcement on Thursday during a briefing at… June 4, 2020 In "News" •Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State LAGOS - Lagos State is considering the full re-opening of the critical sectors of its economy, Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu revealed on Sunday. But the move will not be pushed in a hurry. In the coming days, Sanwo-Olu said the State Government would be rolling… May 17, 2020 In "News" Lagos State government has announced that it will no longer go ahead with its plan to reopen churches and mosques this weekend. Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu announced the indefinite suspension of the plan on Tuesday afternoon during a briefing at the State House, Marina. Details… Source June 16, 2020 In "Politics"